0.1
* initial release
* ignore_lwt option (default true) silently drops MQTT LWT / birth /
  status messages so they don't show up as parse errors.  test mode
  honors the same option and adds --show-status to override.
* compatibility with paho-mqtt 2.x (silences the v1 callback API
  deprecation warning by pinning callback_api_version=VERSION1)
* added _m_s (meters/second) to the unit conversion table -
  Fineoffset-WH24 and similar emit wind_avg_m_s / wind_max_m_s
* sensor_id portion of the tagged tuple now encodes channel as
  <id>:<channel> when the rtl_433 event has a 'channel' field.  lets
  multi-channel sensors (AmbientWeather-WH31E, Acurite Tower, Hideki
  TS04) be pinned by channel with a glob on the id, surviving the
  id-rotates-on-battery-change problem.
* subscribe to an mqtt broker fed by 'rtl_433 -F mqtt'
* standalone test mode that exercises the full parse/map/delta pipeline
  against a live broker, no weewx install required.  --config FILE pulls
  the [RTL433MQTT] section from a weewx.conf-style file.
* generic per-event JSON parsing - no per-sensor classes (the parsing is
  delegated to rtl_433, which already produces decoded fields)
* sensor_map uses <rtl_433_field>.<id>.<model> tuples with glob matching
* unit_system option (US | METRIC) drives both usUnits and automatic
  suffix-based conversion (_C<->_F, _mm<->_in, _km_h<->_mi_h,
  _kph<->_mph, _hPa<->_inHg)
* deltas section converts cumulative counters to per-period values
* basic mqtt auth: host, port, topic, username, password, tls
